Privacy Policy TCDLLC

TCDLLC is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and handle your data when you use Blonk, our virtual reality (VR) game.

1. Information We Collect

When you use Blonk, we may collect the following types of data:

VR Controller Movement Data: Information about the movement of your VR controllers to allow gameplay and improve user experience.

Usernames: Your chosen username for in-game identification and social features.

Audio Data (Microphone): Audio captured through your deviceâ€™s microphone for in-game communication or features.


2. How We Use Your Information

We use your data to:

Provide and improve the gameplay experience.

Enable social and communication features within Blonk(eg-ingame voice chat + usernames).

Monitor and enhance game performance and user engagement.


3. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal information. Data may be shared with trusted partners and service providers solely to operate and improve Blonk.
All third parties adhere to privacy and security standards. Some spesific data may be saved such as ingame usernames
(this is not automatic and is only saved when the user allows by pressing the save button on their username)

4. Data Retention

Your data is retained only as long as necessary to fulfill its intended purpose(eg-ingame usernames) or comply with legal obligations.

5. Your Rights

You have the right to request the deletion of your data. To exercise this right, please contact us at ollie.pearson55@gmail.com with your request and relevant details.
We will process your request as promptly as possible.

6. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted with an updated effective date.

By using Blonk, you agree to this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at ollie.pearson55@gmail.com.

TCDLLC respects your privacy and is committed to safeguarding your personal data.

